and controls. Hunton Services has designed and built skids for gasoline vapor recovery, Ethylene Oxide cooling, shower water cooling, quench tank cooling, acetylene cooling, crude oil cooling, as well as multiple process cooling and/or dehydration.','Process Skids','Process skids are generally application specific and custom-engineered for purpose. ','inherit','closed','closed','','147-revision-v1','','','2018-03-25 02:03:29','2018-03-25 02:03:29','',147,'http://localhost/hunton/147-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(516,1,'2018-03-25 02:03:40','2018-03-25 02:03:40','Pump skids may be configured in several ways; they can be free-standing or integrated with various types of equipment, including chillers, boilers, cooling towers, etc. Hunton Services engineered pump skids are typically provided with hot dipped galvanized structural bases, piping, isolation valves, and a full range of other piping specialties. These skids can also be provided with motor starters, VFDs, instrumentation, and control end devices.','Pump Skids','Pump skids may be configured in several ways; they can be free-standing or integrated with various types of equipment, including chillers, boilers, cooling towers, etc.','inherit','closed','closed','','138-revision-v1','','','2018-03-25 02:03:40','2018-03-25 02:03:40','',138,'http://localhost/hunton/138-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(517,1,'2018-03-25 02:45:01','2018-03-25 02:45:01','','Our Team','','inherit','closed','closed','','48-revision-v1','','','2018-03-25 02:45:01','2018-03-25 02:45:01','',48,'http://localhost/hunton/48-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(518,1,'2018-03-25 02:49:15','2018-03-25 02:49:15','','Blog','','inherit','closed','closed','','26-revision-v1','','','2018-03-25 02:49:15','2018-03-25 02:49:15','',26,'http://localhost/hunton/26-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(519,1,'2018-03-25 19:49:51','2018-03-25 19:49:51','<strong>Our Market Approach:</strong>\r\n\r\nPrescribing Energy Efficiency Measures (EEMs) without understanding the constraints and operational\r\nrequirements of the system delivers failed projects. At Hunton Services we engineer every approach to ensure that the outcomes are measurable and sustainable for the operational life of the project. Understanding the analytics and constraints specific to that application reduces the Total Cost of Ownership.\r\nOur Total Cost of Ownership methodology includes maintenance and system longevity, in-depth calculations, operational savings, and an 8760 hour energy usage analysis. Additionally, key performance indicators such as occupant productivity and market perception can also be articulated.\r\n\r\n<strong>Benefits of Total Cost of Ownership Analysis:</strong>\r\n\r\nHunton Services’ financial and Total Cost of Ownership (TCO) analysis combines proprietary software with over 30 years of real world experience working with both low cost and capital expenditure projects. While the risk of incorrectly implementing a low cost, solution would appear to be minimal, system reliability and building integrity can be compromised by a well-meaning but under qualified implementer.\r\nA capital project also involves much more than the initial first cost of the equipment. In the case of a watercooled chiller purchase, less than 5% of the life-cycle cost of the chiller is the first cost. Without a life-cycle cost analysis, you risk letting the 5% decide for the 95%.\r\n\r\nOur Integrated Systems Approach:\r\nBefore we recommend an EEM, whether an operational change or a capital project, we spend the time to study the possible unintended consequences of the change.\r\n\r\n<em>For example: It may be obvious to many that a lighting retrofit can have a noticeable impact to the cooling requirements of a building. What is less understood is that as buildings continue to improve their design they reduce the outdoor environment’s impact on the sensible cooling load of a building. Simply controlling the temperature in the space no longer guarantees occupant comfort. Spaces may feel humid at previously comfortable temperatures encouraging the space temperature to be lowered to remove the moisture. As many building operators know, this can have the unintended consequence of space heaters being installed under desks - possibly resulting in more energy usage than before the retrofit! Our team of professionals knows how to avoid this trap and maximize comfort while minimizing energy usage.</em>\r\n\r\nFurthermore, we look to utilize technologies provided in one system to improve another. Many modern LED lighting fixtures have occupancy sensors built into them. We can integrate these with the HVAC BAS for operational and efficiency improvements.\r\nHunton Services utilizes DOE approved and analytics driven software to identify retrofit opportunities and improve building systems to achieve maximum efficiency, including:\r\n\r\n• Understanding the goals and budget of our customer\r\n\r\n• <a href=\"http://localhost/hunton/operational-and-efficiency-assessment/\">Profiling system condition and expected life</a>\r\n\r\n• <a href=\"http://localhost/hunton/operational-and-efficiency-assessment/\">Benchmarking energy performance against other buildings</a>\r\n\r\n• Providing a road map to get from the status quo to the end goal\r\n\r\n• <a href=\"http://localhost/hunton/recommissioning-optimization/\">Repairing systems to operate as designed</a>\r\n\r\n• <a href=\"http://localhost/hunton/recommissioning-optimization/\">Implementing improvements to optimize systems beyond their original design</a>\r\n\r\n• <a href=\"http://localhost/hunton/energy-services/ongoing-commissioning/\">Identifying opportunities for operational improvement and preventing system drift</a>','Optimizing Energy Efficiency in Every Market','','publish','closed','closed','','optimizing-energy-efficiency-in-every-market','','','2018-04-10 12:09:42','2018-04-10 12:09:42','',185,'http://localhost/hunton/?page_id=519',9,'page','',0),(520,1,'2018-03-25 19:47:24','2018-03-25 19:47:24','When you choose a Hunton Services audit, one of our energy engineers will visit your site to interview your facility manager, inspect your lighting, air conditioning, heating, and ventilation equipment, controls, refrigeration, air compressors, water consuming equipment, and everything else using energy. Our assessor may  also take measurements of temperatures, pressures, light levels, power draw, and/or other data. In addition, the assessor will ask for permission to get copies of your utility bills and information.\r\nWe’ll then prepare an operational assessment report containing:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">\r\n• A description of the building’s energy consuming equipment\r\n• A description of the equipment including pictures\r\n• An assessment of the condition of the equipment with recommendation</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">\r\no Ongoing Maintenance\r\no Repair\r\no Overhaul/Rehabilitate\r\no Replace</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">\r\n• Estimated usable life remaining\r\n• A budget for items requiring major work during the next 5 years\r\nAdditionally, we’ll include a building level efficiency report containing:\r\n• Calculation of your building’s energy use intensity (EUI)\r\n• Benchmarking data with other similar buildings\r\n• An estimate of the energy and costs savings if the building met an EUI target\r\n• An analysis of the bills to determine whether changing utility rates can provide savings\r\n• A 3D Mapping of your Facility’s Energy Usage (Smart Meter required)\r\n• A description of the building’s energy consuming equipment</p>','Operational and Efficiency Assessment','','publish','closed','closed','','operational-and-efficiency-assessment','','','2018-03-25 20:00:41','2018-03-25 20:00:41','',185,'http://localhost/hunton/?page_id=520',6,'page','',0),(521,1,'2018-03-25 19:47:24','2018-03-25 19:47:24','','Operational and Efficiency Assessment','','inherit','closed','closed','','520-revision-v1','','','2018-03-25 19:47:24','2018-03-25 19:47:24','',520,'http://localhost/hunton/520-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(522,1,'2018-03-25 19:48:10','2018-03-25 19:48:10','<h3>Re/Retro-Commissioning: Repairing a building’s systems to function like they were designed to</h3>\r\nBuilding Commissioning is the preferred method for ensuring that building systems are installed and operating to provide maximum performance and in accordance with project requirements. Architecture and Engineering firms dominate the new construction commissioning market, and for good reason. They act as the owner’s agent – separate from the contract chain – and they have contractors from each trade who are required by the construction contract to make sure the building systems are operating as designed.\r\n\r\nHunton Services believes that after an Efficiency Assessment, Re/Retro-Commissioning (RCx) projects are the ideal second step to take when looking to upgrade a building’s systems. For many owners with inhouse service teams Architecture and Engineering firms have made excellent choice for a RCx agent. However, our customers who lack the staff to implement the recommendations often feel they end up with a report of things that are wrong, but with no action plan to fix them. Our team of engineers and analysts working alongside our technicians, allows a Hunton Services RCx report to identify what is wrong, explain why fixing it is important, and provide a proposal for us to fix it.\r\n<h3>\r\nHunton Services Engineered Site Assessment: Optimizing a building’s systems beyond the original design</h3>\r\nThe purpose of commissioning is to repair a building’s systems to function like they were designed to, but the functional needs of a building change over time. Where an Engineered Site Assessment differs from traditional commissioning is we will also provide a description of feasible energy efficiency measures (EEMs) you may wish to consider implementing.\r\n\r\nEach of these measures are developed such that the report includes:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">• A description of existing conditions\r\n• A description of the proposed EEM\r\n• Expected Annual savings associated with the EEM\r\n• Expected cost to implement the EEM\r\n• Simple payback or Return on Investment calculations</p>\r\nWe provide Commissioning and Engineered Site Assessments for the following Systems:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">• Lighting systems\r\n• HVAC Systems and Controls\r\n• Compressed Air Systems\r\n• Electric Motors and Drives\r\n• Process Systems\r\n• Steam Systems\r\n• Heat Recovery\r\n• Renewable Energy Applications\r\n• Building Envelope Upgrades</p>','Recommissioning & Optimization','','publish','closed','closed','','recommissioning-optimization','','','2018-04-10 12:22:21','2018-04-10 12:22:21','',185,'http://localhost/hunton/?page_id=522',3,'page','',0),(523,1,'2018-03-25 19:48:10','2018-03-25 19:48:10','','Recommissioning & Optimization page','','inherit','closed','closed','','522-revision-v1','','','2018-03-25 19:48:10','2018-03-25 19:48:10','',522,'http://localhost/hunton/522-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(524,1,'2018-03-25 19:48:34','2018-03-25 19:48:34','','Recommissioning & Optimization','','inherit','closed','closed','','522-revision-v1','','','2018-03-25 19:48:34','2018-03-25 19:48:34','',522,'http://localhost/hunton/522-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(525,1,'2018-03-25 19:49:17','2018-03-25 19:49:17','<h3>Making Data Actionable</h3>\r\nToday’s automation systems give building operators an abundance of data. Often there is so much data that most building operators only have time to check two or three data points with any regularity. The rest of the data is stored for a 30-day cycle until there is a failure of some kind, and then the service company for that system will look for the data they need to diagnose the issue. It is usually at this point that the owner discovers they aren’t storing the right BAS points or they are storing them at a time interval that makes it virtually worthless for identifying the root cause.\r\n\r\nAfter years of dealing with this issue, <a href=\"http://localhost/hunton/energy-services/operational-and-efficiency-assessment/\">Hunton Services</a> began fielding an analytics program that has been developed to comb through the massive amount of BAS points, provide a grade to various systems and components, allow analysts and engineers to dive in deeper, change point sampling rates to something frequent enough to be useful, and ultimately report back to the owner with functional improvements to their system.\r\n\r\nAccording to research from Texas A&amp;M University and the Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory, the result of operational wear and tear – known as drift – buildings can see energy efficiencies degrade by 10% to 30% over a one- to two-year period.\r\n\r\nTo prevent this, we implement a process known as Ongoing Commissioning. Instead of allowing a system to drift from proper operation over the course of years, Hunton Services will implement an Ongoing Commissioning plan which utilizes our analytics programs to identify and correct drift. At the same time the system finds new operational improvements that when implemented make each system more efficient, ultimately driving down the operational costs of a building, instead of allowing them to drift up.\r\n<h3>Hunton Services can provide Dynamic Commissioning within the following building sub-systems:</h3>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">• Heating, ventilating, air conditioning, refrigeration and their associated controls systems\r\n• Lighting systems\r\n• Domestic hot water systems\r\n• Plumbing systems\r\n• Building envelope systems\r\n• IT Systems and building networks</p>','Ongoing Commissioning','','publish','closed','closed','','ongoing-commissioning','','','2018-04-10 12:21:13','2018-04-10 12:21:13','',185,'http://localhost/hunton/?page_id=525',2,'page','',0),(526,1,'2018-03-25 19:49:17','2018-03-25 19:49:17','','Ongoing Commissioning','','inherit','closed','closed','','525-revision-v1','','','2018-03-25 19:49:17','2018-03-25 19:49:17','',525,'http://localhost/hunton/525-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(528,1,'2018-03-25 19:49:51','2018-03-25 19:49:51','<strong>Our Market Approach:</strong>\r\n\r\nPrescribing Energy Efficiency Measures (EEMs) without understanding the constraints and operational\r\nrequirements of the system delivers failed projects. At Hunton Services we engineer every approach to ensure that the outcomes are measurable and sustainable for the operational life of the project. Understanding the analytics and constraints specific to that application reduces the Total Cost of Ownership.\r\nOur Total Cost of Ownership methodology includes maintenance and system longevity, in-depth calculations, operational savings, and an 8760 hour energy usage analysis. Additionally, key performance indicators such as occupant productivity and market perception can also be articulated.\r\n\r\n<strong>Benefits of Total Cost of Ownership Analysis:</strong>\r\n\r\nHunton Services’ financial and Total Cost of Ownership (TCO) analysis combines proprietary software with over 30 years of real world experience working with both low cost and capital expenditure projects. While the risk of incorrectly implementing a low cost, solution would appear to be minimal, system reliability and building integrity can be compromised by a well-meaning but under qualified implementer.\r\nA capital project also involves much more than the initial first cost of the equipment. In the case of a watercooled chiller purchase, less than 5% of the life-cycle cost of the chiller is the first cost. Without a life-cycle cost analysis, you risk letting the 5% decide for the 95%.\r\n\r\nOur Integrated Systems Approach:\r\nBefore we recommend an EEM, whether an operational change or a capital project, we spend the time to study the possible unintended consequences of the change.\r\n\r\n<em>For example: It may be obvious to many that a lighting retrofit can have a noticeable impact to the cooling requirements of a building. What is less understood is that as buildings continue to improve their design they reduce the outdoor environment’s impact on the sensible cooling load of a building. Simply controlling the temperature in the space no longer guarantees occupant comfort. Spaces may feel humid at previously comfortable temperatures encouraging the space temperature to be lowered to remove the moisture. As many building operators know, this can have the unintended consequence of space heaters being installed under desks - possibly resulting in more energy usage than before the retrofit! Our team of professionals knows how to avoid this trap and maximize comfort while minimizing energy usage.</em>\r\n\r\nFurthermore, we look to utilize technologies provided in one system to improve another. Many modern LED lighting fixtures have occupancy sensors built into them. We can integrate these with the HVAC BAS for operational and efficiency improvements.\r\nHunton Services utilizes DOE approved and analytics driven software to identify retrofit opportunities and improve building systems to achieve maximum efficiency, including:\r\n\r\n• Understanding the goals and budget of our customer\r\n\r\n• <a href=\"http://localhost/hunton/operational-and-efficiency-assessment/\">Profiling system condition and expected life</a>\r\n\r\n• <a href=\"http://localhost/hunton/operational-and-efficiency-assessment/\">Benchmarking energy performance against other buildings</a>\r\n\r\n• Providing a road map to get from the status quo to the end goal\r\n\r\n• <a href=\"http://localhost/hunton/recommissioning-optimization/\">Repairing systems to operate as designed</a>\r\n\r\n• <a href=\"http://localhost/hunton/recommissioning-optimization/\">Implementing improvements to optimize systems beyond their original design</a>\r\n\r\n• <a href=\"http://localhost/hunton/energy-services/ongoing-commissioning/\">Identifying opportunities for operational improvement and preventing system drift</a>','Optimizing Energy Efficiency in Every Market','','inherit','closed','closed','','519-revision-v1','','','2018-03-25 19:49:51','2018-03-25 19:49:51','',519,'http://localhost/hunton/519-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(530,1,'2018-03-25 19:50:51','2018-03-25 19:50:51','When you choose a Hunton Services audit, one of our energy engineers will visit your site to interview your facility manager, inspect your lighting, air conditioning, heating, and ventilation equipment, controls, refrigeration, air compressors, water consuming equipment, and everything else using energy. Our assessor may  also take measurements of temperatures, pressures, light levels, power draw, and/or other data. In addition, the assessor will ask for permission to get copies of your utility bills and information.\r\nWe’ll then prepare an operational assessment report containing:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">\r\n• A description of the building’s energy consuming equipment\r\n• A description of the equipment including pictures\r\n• An assessment of the condition of the equipment with recommendation</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">\r\no Ongoing Maintenance\r\no Repair\r\no Overhaul/Rehabilitate\r\no Replace</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">\r\n• Estimated usable life remaining\r\n• A budget for items requiring major work during the next 5 years\r\nAdditionally, we’ll include a building level efficiency report containing:\r\n• Calculation of your building’s energy use intensity (EUI)\r\n• Benchmarking data with other similar buildings\r\n• An estimate of the energy and costs savings if the building met an EUI target\r\n• An analysis of the bills to determine whether changing utility rates can provide savings\r\n• A 3D Mapping of your Facility’s Energy Usage (Smart Meter required)\r\n• A description of the building’s energy consuming equipment</p>','Operational and Efficiency Assessment','','inherit','closed','closed','','520-revision-v1','','','2018-03-25 19:50:51','2018-03-25 19:50:51','',520,'http://localhost/hunton/520-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(531,1,'2018-03-25 19:53:49','2018-03-25 19:53:49','Re/Retro-Commissioning: Repairing a building’s systems to function like they were designed to Building Commissioning is the preferred method for ensuring that building systems are installed and operating to provide maximum performance and in accordance with project requirements. Architecture and Engineering firms dominate the new construction commissioning market, and for good reason. They act as the owner’s agent –\nseparate from the contract chain – and they have contractors from each trade who are required by the construction contract to make sure the building systems are operating as designed.\n\nHunton Services believes that after an Efficiency Assessment, Re/Retro-Commissioning (RCx) projects are the ideal second step to take when looking to upgrade a building’s systems. For many owners with inhouse service teams Architecture and Engineering firms have made excellent choice for a RCx agent. However, our customers who lack the staff to implement the recommendations often feel they end up with a report of things that are wrong, but with no action plan to fix them. Our team of engineers and analysts working alongside our technicians, allows a Hunton Services RCx report to identify what is wrong, explain why fixing it is important, and provide a proposal for us to fix it.\n<strong>Hunton Services Engineered Site Assessment:</strong> Optimizing a building’s systems beyond the original design\n\nThe purpose of commissioning is to repair a building’s systems to function like they were designed to, but the functional needs of a building change over time. Where an Engineered Site Assessment differs from traditional commissioning is we will also provide a description of feasible energy efficiency measures (EEMs) you may wish to consider implementing.\n\nEach of the